images.description: My Fruity passed on just recently but she was the cutest cat ever! Look at her being modest and covering her lady bits.

This is the day I let her go. She was only 4.2 pounds and going into shut down. It was hard cuz she was still bright and responsive when she had the energy to be awake but she had all but stopped eating and drinking. She had had such a sharp decline with in just a few days that I knew it was time.
Her and Oct begging for pets. Don't worry they got them and some treats. Oct is a handsome boy too

images.description:
My son has loved cats since he was 2 years old and his uncle gave him a stuffed toy cat as a Yule gift. 
When kitten Charlie (Miss Charlotta) moved in with us on 12-12-2012, he soon became her Favourite Human (story here: https://imgur.com/gallery/kB8siPM )
Charlie isn't fond of being held or hugged, but her Favourite Human is awarded special privileges.

Unfortunately FH had to move far away, first for studies and then for work.
Thanks to Sweden's generous vacation laws, FH comes home to his kitty twice a year, two weeks at Yule and two weeks in the summer.

images.description: Apologies for the 'me' in this pic, but the day Mr G flopped on his back under my arm in bed, my heart melted.

He learned food was always available, he could sleep as much as he liked without fear, and how to find his inner kitten when playing. 2.5 years or more on the streets fending for himself meant he was suspicious of humans. It took 9 months before he'd let me approach and touch him. The day he turned up sick with a massive abscess on his head was the day I took him to the vet. A post on the local FB group soon got attention, and Gingernuts' story unfolded. 

My Vet contacted the 'owner', who lied through her teeth, so the Vet got her to hand over ownership or pay a huge vet bill. Thankfully, the wretched woman agreed, and his microchip was changed to my name. Vetwork and desexing done, he recuperated at home. I had no idea how he'd adapt to being an indoors cat, but he took to the litterbox immediately and has been a flawless kitty from the get-go. He's my world now.
Now re-named 'Mister G' since he no longer has any ginger nuts (haha), he is my most treasured possession.

images.description: Meet Olive! She's an energetic 4 month old terror, er, kitten. Her favorite hobbies include ninja attacking the other kitten, and nibbling on my fingers (only my fingers, she won't do that to my husband). She can be a cuddle bug, but kitten energy has her constantly running around. Her favorite toys are whatever the other kitten (Hamilton) is playing with.
Just enjoying the sun, and spying on the neighbors.
She stole it!
